        headingEn: 'Background',
        body: '''Menurut Theogonia karya Hesiodos, alam semesta bermula dari Khaos, lalu lahir Gaia (Bumi) dan Uranus (Langit). Dari pasangan itu lahir dua belas Titan. Uranus membenci anak-anaknya dan memenjarakan mereka di dalam tubuh Gaia. Karena tersiksa, Gaia menempa sabit dan meminta anak-anaknya membalas. Hanya Cronus, Titan bungsu, yang berani. Ia mengebiri ayahnya dan merebut takhta langit. Namun Cronus meniru kekejaman ayahnya: karena diramalkan akan digulingkan oleh anaknya sendiri, ia menelan setiap bayi yang dilahirkan istrinya, Rhea. Hestia, Demeter, Hera, Hades, dan Poseidon semuanya ditelan hidup-hidup, menanamkan benih dendam yang kelak meledak menjadi perang para dewa.''',
        bodyEn: '''According to Hesiod\'s Theogony, the universe began with Chaos, from which arose Gaia (Earth) and Uranus (Sky). From their union came the twelve Titans. Uranus hated his children and imprisoned them within Gaia\'s body. Tormented, Gaia forged a sickle and begged her children to take revenge. Only Cronus, the youngest Titan, dared. He castrated his father and seized the throne of heaven. Yet Cronus repeated his father\'s cruelty: warned by a prophecy that his own child would overthrow him, he swallowed each infant his wife Rhea bore. Hestia, Demeter, Hera, Hades, and Poseidon were all swallowed alive, planting the seeds of a vengeance that would one day erupt into a war of the gods.''',
