        bodyEn: '''With this victory, the young gods confirmed Zeus as king of heaven and supreme ruler. The age of the Titans ended, replaced by the age of the Olympian gods. Yet the triumph did not fully end all challenges. Gaia, enraged that her Titan children were imprisoned, would later bear the Giants and the monster Typhon to challenge Zeus in the Gigantomachy. Even so, the Titanomachy marked the founding of a new cosmic order that would endure throughout Greek mythology. Zeus then shared power with his brothers by drawing lots, ensuring a collective rule that replaced the sole tyranny of Cronus. Out of chaos came order, and out of the war of the gods came the cosmos known to mortals.''',
