    impact: '''Titanomakhia mengakhiri kekuasaan para Titan dan mendirikan pemerintahan para dewa Olimpus yang dipimpin Zeus. Para Titan yang kalah dikurung di Tartarus dijaga para Hekatonkheir, sementara Atlas dihukum memanggul langit. Kemenangan ini menetapkan Zeus sebagai raja kosmos dan membuka jalan bagi pembagian tiga alam. Namun kemarahan Gaia atas kekalahan itu melahirkan ancaman baru berupa Gigantes dan Typhon, sehingga perang bukan akhir dari konflik kosmis, melainkan awal dari zaman baru yang harus terus dipertahankan.''',
    impactEn: '''The Titanomachy ended the rule of the Titans and established the government of the Olympian gods under Zeus. The defeated Titans were confined in Tartarus, guarded by the Hecatoncheires, while Atlas was condemned to bear the sky. This victory fixed Zeus as king of the cosmos and paved the way for the division of the three realms. Yet Gaia\'s anger over the defeat gave rise to new threats in the Giants and Typhon, so the war was not the end of cosmic conflict but the beginning of a new age that had to be continually defended.''',
    meaning: '''Titanomakhia melambangkan peralihan dari kekuatan alam yang liar dan kacau menuju keteraturan, hukum, dan keadilan yang diwakili para dewa Olimpus. Pola pemberontakan anak melawan ayah, dari Uranus ke Cronus ke Zeus, menggambarkan siklus kekuasaan dan pembaruan. Bagi orang Yunani kuno, kisah ini menjelaskan mengapa kosmos tertata seperti sekarang dan mengesahkan wibawa Zeus. Tema perang antargenerasi dewa ini kelak memengaruhi banyak mitologi lain, termasuk kisah penciptaan Timur Dekat, dan menjadi model klasik tentang tegaknya ketertiban atas kekacauan.''',
    meaningEn: '''The Titanomachy symbolizes the transition from wild, chaotic natural forces to the order, law, and justice embodied by the Olympian gods. The pattern of sons rebelling against fathers, from Uranus to Cronus to Zeus, depicts a cycle of power and renewal. For the ancient Greeks, the tale explained why the cosmos is ordered as it is and legitimized the authority of Zeus. This theme of a war between generations of gods would later influence many other mythologies, including Near Eastern creation stories, and became a classic model of order triumphing over chaos.''',
