        body: '''Setelah Titanomakhia berakhir, tiga putra Cronus yang telah menumbangkan ayah mereka menghadapi pertanyaan besar: siapa yang berhak memerintah kosmos yang baru? Zeus, Poseidon, dan Hades adalah pahlawan utama perang itu, masing-masing memegang senjata tempaan Kiklops. Untuk menghindari perpecahan dan perang saudara di antara para pemenang, mereka sepakat membagi wilayah pemerintahan. Dalam Iliad karya Homeros, Poseidon sendiri menceritakan bahwa dunia dibagi menjadi tiga bagian. Keputusan tidak diambil berdasarkan paksaan atau senioritas semata, melainkan melalui undian yang adil, sebuah cara khas Yunani untuk menyerahkan keputusan penting kepada kehendak takdir agar tak seorang pun merasa dicurangi.''',
        bodyEn: '''After the Titanomachy ended, the three sons of Cronus who had toppled their father faced a great question: who had the right to rule the new cosmos? Zeus, Poseidon, and Hades were the chief heroes of that war, each wielding a weapon forged by the Cyclopes. To avoid division and civil war among the victors, they agreed to divide the domains of rule. In Homer\'s Iliad, Poseidon himself recounts that the world was split into three parts. The decision was not made by force or mere seniority, but through a fair drawing of lots, a characteristically Greek way of surrendering an important decision to the will of fate so that no one would feel cheated.''',
