    impact: '''Pembagian tiga alam menetapkan struktur kekuasaan yang menopang seluruh mitologi Yunani. Zeus menjadi raja langit, Poseidon penguasa laut, dan Hades penjaga dunia bawah, sementara bumi tetap wilayah bersama. Kesepakatan ini mencegah perang saudara di antara para pemenang Titanomakhia dan menciptakan tatanan kolektif yang stabil. Namun batas kekuasaan itu tak selalu damai; ketegangan antara Zeus dan Poseidon berulang kali muncul. Kerangka tiga alam inilah yang menjadi panggung bagi hampir setiap kisah dewa, pahlawan, dan manusia dalam mitologi Yunani selanjutnya.''',
    impactEn: '''The division of the three realms established the power structure that underpins all Greek mythology. Zeus became king of the sky, Poseidon lord of the sea, and Hades keeper of the underworld, while the earth remained common ground. This agreement prevented civil war among the victors of the Titanomachy and created a stable collective order. Yet those boundaries were not always peaceful; tension between Zeus and Poseidon arose repeatedly. It is this framework of three realms that became the stage for nearly every tale of gods, heroes, and mortals in the mythology that followed.''',
    meaning: '''Kisah undian tiga alam melambangkan gagasan bahwa kekuasaan sah lahir dari kesepakatan dan takdir, bukan semata paksaan. Bagi orang Yunani, undian adalah cara adil membagi hak, mencerminkan nilai demokratis dan keseimbangan. Ketiga alam, langit, laut, dan dunia bawah, memetakan seluruh pengalaman manusia tentang kosmos: yang di atas, yang mengelilingi, dan yang menanti setelah mati. Pola tiga penguasa bersaudara ini menggemakan mitos Timur Dekat dan menjadi model tentang bagaimana ketertiban dunia dibangun melalui pembagian peran, bukan monopoli tunggal, sehingga wibawa Zeus pun tetap terikat batas.''',
    meaningEn: '''The tale of the lots over the three realms symbolizes the idea that legitimate power arises from agreement and fate, not mere force. For the Greeks, casting lots was a fair way of dividing rights, reflecting values of balance and even democracy. The three realms, sky, sea, and underworld, map the whole human experience of the cosmos: what is above, what surrounds, and what awaits after death. This pattern of three ruling brothers echoes Near Eastern myth and became a model for how the world\'s order is built through a sharing of roles rather than a single monopoly, so that even Zeus\'s authority remained bound by limits.''',
